Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26th: The excellent returning migrant workers into a rural revitalization force
Zhang Xiongjia, 34, is in the orchard village of Meishan City, Sichuan Province, and in 2010 he quit his job with a monthly salary of tens of thousands of yuan in Beijing to start a business.
After several years of hard work, he now runs a grape growing family farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, becoming a well-known leader of wealth, and has also been selected to enter the village "two committees" team.
In recent years, under the inspiration of a series of national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization policies, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home and start a business, which has activated a spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a large population province in western China and a large labor export province, has implemented the "Excellent Migrant Workers Revitalization Training Project" due to snobbish guidance, and in 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were generated from the outstanding migrant workers, cultivated 61,000 village reserve forces, and developed more than 20,000 party members, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
The key is not well-off, the key is to look at the fellow countrymen.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged workers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it has also led to the emergence of "hollowing out" in rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations, and the village party branch secretaries and party members have shown the characteristics of "one old and one low", that is, aging age, low education, and the village party organization leaders are not strong, and the problem of not connecting.
If elements such as rural talents have been flowing to the city in one direction, the countryside has long been in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia", and revitalization is an empty phrase.
Attracting those migrant workers who have the ability, awareness and ambition to serve their hometowns, and guide them to return home to become rich leaders, train them into party members and rural cadres, and enrich the grassroots cadres from them, which is the solution to the fundamentals of rural party members and grass-roots party organizations.
Good migrant workers can be brought back, but also let them stay and do well.
In recent years, Sichuan has begun to pay close attention to the construction of the peasant labor force, and on the basis of strict selection criteria, it has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted return, service guarantee, training, and selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their ability, work, and have hope in life.
This year is the end of the decisive battle against poverty, and talents are the key factor in connecting poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, they should be built into a task force and a living force that can stay, fight and take away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation and development and revitalization.
