Beijing's natural ecology continues to improve, attracting more than 500 kinds of wildlife cities "settled"
2020-07-26 05:03:17 Source:Beijing Youth Daily Author:Wang Sisuo Responsibility Editor:Wang Sisuo
The natural ecology of the capital continues to improve, attracting the "settlement" of wildlife cities
There are more than 500 species of wild animals in Beijing.
Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the Municipal Landscaping Bureau that in recent years, with the continuous improvement of the natural ecological environment of the capital, the types and number of wild animals have also continued to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife living in Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including national-level protected animals such as brown horse chicken and black stork, as well as secondary protected animals such as wildebeest, large swans, gray cranes and emu.
Whether it is planting a city forest in the second ring, or embedded in the small micro-wetland between the buildings, it not only brings the wild fun of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attracts wild animals to "settlement" in the city.
In the mid-summer season, it is located in Songshan National Nature Reserve in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District.
One of them played quietly by the side of the mountain, and the two dogs fought each other.
In the back, a wild boar can't help but "stitch" on his body and is tucking on the bark. Hu Qiaoli, director of Songshan National Nature Reserve Management Department, said that as of the end of 2019, in this green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares, there are 178 kinds of wild animals, including national-level protection animal spoon chickens and wildebeest, and nearly one-third of the city's wildlife species can be seen here.
"In Songshan, wild animals are the real 'owners', and our staff can only be regarded as the 'guards' of the family."
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the situation of wild animals and plants in the protected area on the ground, more than 30 professional patrolmen every day, along 16 carefully formulated protection routes, and there will be a "turning circle" every month, and almost all the entire protected area is used for a whole day.
“In the inspection, not only to check and record biodiversity, but also to inspect the installation of artificial nests, to rescue injured wild animals, to install infrared cameras in the field, etc.”
Songshan National Nature Reserve has now installed more than 200 infrared cameras to record the living conditions of wild animals in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli introduced that with the continuous enrichment of the biodiversity of the protected area in recent years, more and more wild animals appear in the camera, and the leopard cats, sturgeons and pig badxes have become "resident guests", and the "appearance rate" of the national second-class protected animal antelope is also getting higher and higher.
Zhang Zhiming, director of the wildlife and wetland protection department of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Landscaping, said that Beijing's terrestrial vertebrate wildlife has increased from 461 species in 1994 to more than 500 now, and the variety and number of wild animals in Beijing has continued to increase in recent years.
The presence of wild animals in cities is becoming more and more common, which is closely related to the continuous upgrading of urban greening in the capital in recent years
In particular, a new round of afforestation and greening construction of millions of acres began in 2018, proposing to reshape the urban ecological environment, improve the ecological function of forest green land, and highlight the concept of "near nature".
The plan strives to achieve interconnection and interaction with the surrounding green space, so that wild animals can "go to relatives and friends", and the trees planted are also honey sources and food-based plants that animals love.
Black land "plants" agricultural modernization - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26th: Black land "plants" agricultural modernization
In the summer, two spraying pharmaceutical aircraft passed from the 10,000 mu high-yield demonstration field of the second working station of the fifth management area of the Friendship Farm, forming two white lines, and the "first in the world" in the green field with black rice seedlings was particularly eye-catching.
Kong Lingqiang, the station manager of this operation station, said that this aircraft can spray more than 6,000 acres of arable land a day, which is about eight times more efficient than drones and hundreds of times that of artificial labor.
This farm is located in the territory of Heilongjiang Province, China's first grain-producing province, from the past "snap" rice cutting sound through to today's "rumbling" motor sound, Chinese traditional farming and farms in this black soil belt to achieve metabolism.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farms.
Kong Lingqiang introduced that on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural input, and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the level of standardized operation of agricultural machinery in the field.
In this year's rice production process, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned cutting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes the planting of seedlings more uniform, which can maximize the use of sunlight and cultivated land resources, and save 16 yuan per acre in labor costs.
The farm tries new technologies such as informationization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total number of farm machinery is 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate of the field is 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operations achieve 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision seeding in dry fields, and 100% of dryfield high-power locomotives.
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture, and digital agriculture are the path of agricultural modernization."
Liu Hualian, director of Friendship Farm, said.
The key to agricultural modernization is scientific and technological progress.
In recent years, Heilongjiang agricultural reclamation, represented by farms, has played a leading role in modern large-scale agricultural "carrier" demonstration and leading, and has initially established a modern agricultural industry system led by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrialization.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery Expo Park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
Here, more than 140 agricultural tools (pieces) have been introduced and used by Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation for many years.
These agricultural tools and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
