International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious problems in bilateral relations between China and the United States, and it is legitimate and necessary for China to respond to unreasonable provocations by the United States and take countermeasures.
Andrés Bolkes, director of the China Studies Center at the Institute of International Studies at the University of Chile, said that the unilateral measures of the United States have undermined the bridge of understanding between the two peoples and put the relationship between the two countries in crisis.
China's notification of the U.S. closure of its consulate in Chengdu is a counter to U.S. unilateral measures and in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Justo, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Center for Arab-Chinese Studies, believes that China's decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure against the United States' previous provocations, and is not aimed at ordinary Americans.
The United States is trying to divert the attention of the American people by pressuring China to cover up its weak response to the new crown epidemic.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Indonesian think tank Asian Innovation Research Center, said that the provocative diplomatic posture of the United States has caused serious problems for the relations between China and the United States, and the relations between the two countries are facing serious challenges.
China's notification of the closure of the US Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal counter-measure, which is in line with diplomatic practice, which reflects China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests and reflects the rational and favorable nature of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian current affairs commentator Francis Semwinza said that China's decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the US provocation.
If China-US relations should return to normal, the US should take the initiative to improve relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve economic and political win-win results with China, and how to benefit the two peoples and the entire international community.
Ali Yusuf, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab-China Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures China was forced to take were a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the United States, in line with international law and basic norms of international relations, and in line with diplomatic practice.
Earlier, the US request to close the Chinese Consulate General in Houston seriously violated international law and basic norms governing international relations.
It is hoped that the US side will rescind the relevant previous decision and create the necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore's "Lianhe Zaobao" published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the United States' efforts, although China is very reluctant to see the deterioration of China-US relations, it has to take countermeasures.
