"Shangjiang South" in pursuit of poetic "Yellow River Dream"-Zhongxin.com
(China's poverty reduction story) "Shangjiang South" pursues the poetic "Yellow River Dream"
Xinhua News Agency Yinchuan July 26 (Yang Di) "Nine songs of the Yellow River, the waves of the wind from the end of the world."
The Yellow River, which aroused countless venerations and sons, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain, now known as "Shangjiang South", Ningxia is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
The “Dream of the River Clear Water Show”
"The world's Yellow River Funingxia", the Yellow River through Ningxia 397 km, is the "mother river" of the parenting side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development and utilization of rivers and lakes and the protection of management are unbalanced, and the chaos of excessive sewage discharge, the construction of fields in the lake, and the encroachment of the waters have emerged, resulting in black and odorous water, excessive water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of water ecological diversity and striving to return the Yellow River to clear the water show.
Water should be treated from the source.
In Ningxia Yinchuan, the local government adopts the method of "standardizing + pollution control + strict control", the sewage in the industrial park is all centralized treatment, the urban sewage treatment plant has all achieved the first level A standard discharge, and the black and odorous water body in the urban built-up area has been basically eliminated, and the third batch of China's black and odorous water demonstration cities has been successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake long system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake long system of district, city and county, and the long river patrol has become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, who lives in a village on the Yellow River, witnessed the change of the Yellow River: “The water smelled like before, and there was no smell after rectification.”
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is good, his life is more comfortable, and now he often goes to the Yellow River with his family for a walk and feels the blue sky.
The “Wetland Dream” of Sandgulls
Birds, green trees, stacks, turquoise water... Fan Zhongyan's beautiful scenery of "sand gulls" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River has formed a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and the ecological balance of water resources, and has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, the relevant departments of Ningxia have invested a total of about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects, at present, Yinchuan wetland area of 19,200 hectares, wetland protection rate of 78.5%, there are natural lakes, swamp wetlands nearly 200, with 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks, 8 municipal parks.
Lv Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Conservation Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds, "the gull is an endangered bird, there are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which Yinchuan wetlands are inhabited by more than 2,000."
At the same time, Ningxia has delineated a red line of 500 meters for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, and stipulates that in addition to public welfare projects, no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, introduced that through pollution source control, comprehensive remediation of river and lake ecology and end-to-end wetland construction, the water quality of Ningxia's 9 main into the yellow drain has reached 100% of the Class IV standard, "Now the water is also clear, the fish also swims, and the flowers are also opened."
The “drinking dream” of people’s livelihood
Ningxia Yinchuan City once had an "embarrassing" title: the only city in the yellow city that "guarded the Yellow River to water and drink".
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing the problem of water shortage at the peak of the summer, and the "pain of water shortage" in the past ten years has become the summer pain experience of many high-rise residents, but in the major water sources, the urban underground has formed a large area of groundwater over-harvesting funnel area, and the water shortage has become a problem that plagues Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, the water of the Yellow River after drinking purification has become a good way to solve the problem of drinking water for local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Municipal Water Bureau, introduced that in order to improve the domestic and rural production and water demand of Yinchuan urban and rural residents, Ningxia timely launched the Yinchuan metropolitan area urban and rural western water supply project, replacing the original groundwater source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially to Yinchuan City, the three districts of water, in 2020, Minning Town, Helan County residents also drink the Yellow River water."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will consider the transformation of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply integration, "the next step, we will integrate the rural scattered water supply points into the western water supply project, is expected to basically achieve the integration of urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan by the end of this year."
