Shenzhen on the introduction of health regulations for public comments - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporter Mao Siqiang, Bai Yu) encourages residents to do medical examinations and early detection of problems; prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establish an online game health review system; employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel... Recently, the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Draft for Comment) were officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law".
In order to encourage residents to do physical examination and detect problems early, the above-mentioned consultation draft proposes that the health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health examination projects according to different age, occupation and other factors.
The cost of the health examination within the scope of the basic catalogue of the health examination project shall be paid by the Social Health Insurance Coordinated Fund according to the standard of once a year per person.
The draft for comment makes it clear that the employer should rationally allocate human resources, arrange staff working hours, and implement a rest system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor load, avoid excessive loss of human function or physical and mental health damage to employees' health, and strictly implement the staff paid leave system.
In addition, the employer should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and regularly organize employee health examination.
In terms of the physical and mental health of minors, the draft for comment proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, and the sales location of alcoholic beverages is restricted, and for violations of the provisions, the market supervision and management department will order the correction and impose a fine of 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "banning alcohol", minors also need to "multiple sports".
According to the requirements of the draft for comment, the school should arrange students' sports activities for more than one hour a day.
For online games, public security, cultural radio and television tourism and sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the Internet Internet service business place health supervision system, establish an online game health review system, and create a good communication space and communication culture for the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the draft also proposed that flu patients must wear masks in public places, and medical and health institutions will disclose patients' privacy without consent to fine 20,000 yuan.
It is worth noting that in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should evaluate the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population before formulating plans and plans, normative documents such as urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and ecological environment protection, biopharmaceutical industry development, and approval of major construction projects and major public service projects.
If it is not evaluated or evaluated will have a serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents, it shall not be formulated or approved for implementation.
