Cocosiri Tibetan antelope enters the return season - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, July 25 (Reporter Wang Jinjin) The reporter learned from the five beam protection stations of the Cocosiri Management Office of the Yangtze River Source Park of the Sanjiangyuan National Park Administration that the monitoring shows that the Tibetan antelopes that had migrated to the lake area in the hinterland of Cocosiri were ending the birth of the litter and began to return to their original habitat with the cubs.
Surveillance footage near the protection station of Wudao Liang shows that on July 25, about 40 female Tibetan antelopes led three Tibetan antelope cubs to pass the 3002 km of the Qinghai-Tibet Highway and the five-way girder North Bridge of the Qinghai-Tibet Railway, and the Tibetan antelopes have begun to move back.
According to expert analysis, in recent years, the number of Tibetan antelope cubs in the returning flock has accounted for one-fourth to one-fifth of the total number of Tibetan antelope sheep.
Lian Xinming, an associate researcher at the Northwest Plateau Biology Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said: "In the early stage of the migration, the Tibetan antelope faces a higher risk of being eaten, so the number of cubs in the flock will be relatively small, and there may even be no cubs."
According to the statistics of the Cocosiri Management Office of the Yangtze River Source Park of the Sanjiangyuan National Park Administration, the overall number of Tibetan antelopes has been increasing year by year, and the number of Tibetan antelopes in 2019 was 4,860, an increase of 338 over 2018.
Lian Xinming said: "It is expected that the return of Tibetan antelopes will end in early September this year, and the number of returning Tibetan antelopes is still expected to continue to increase."
Tibetan antelopes are protected animals at the national level.
Every year at the end of May, Tibetan antelopes from the Sanjiangyuan of Qinghai, Qiangtang in Tibet, and Aljinshan in Xinjiang go to the Antelope Lake in the hinterland of Cocosiri.
Wu Xiaomin, a Tibetan antelope conservation expert in China and a researcher at the Shaanxi Provincial Institute of Zoology (Northwest Endangered Animal Research Institute), said: "The return of the Tibetan antelope is the process of returning to the habitat with the cub after the end of the litter. At first, the return group that left the littering area is relatively large, but then the Tibetan antelope will return to their respective habitats according to different geographical populations and different paths."
In order to ensure the safe return of the Tibetan sheep, the reporter learned that the Cocosiri Management Office of the Yangtze River Source Park of the Sanjiangyuan National Park has arranged for staff to continue to carry out video monitoring and district patrols in the main relocation area.
If it is found that the Tibetan Antelope sheep is trying to cross the road, the patrol team will carry out temporary traffic control in the first time, so that the sheep can pass through the wildlife passageway safely, so as to ensure that it is as little as possible disturbed by humans on the way back.
So, how to relieve the heat in daily life?
Experts suggest that summer go out as far as possible to avoid the high temperature period, it is best not to walk or work in the hot sun around noon, because the sun during this time period is the strongest, the possibility of heat stroke is higher.
If you must go out at this time, be sure to do a good job of protection, such as wearing umbrellas, wearing sun hats, wearing sunglasses, the best conditions to apply sunscreen, to prevent sunburn.
Clothes try to use light color, good breathability of cotton, hemp, silk texture, less wearing chemical fiber clothing, so as not to avoid a lot of sweating can not timely heat dissipation, causing heat stroke.
When the hot and hot weather, prepare enough water to drink, drink in time, do not wait for thirst before drinking water, because once you feel thirsty, your body has water shortage, each time you drink 150 ml to 200 ml, drink warm water, do not drink ice water.
According to the temperature, the average person drinks 1.5 to 2 liters of water per day, and high-temperature workers drink 3 to 5 liters of water per day.
When sweating more, some salt water can be added appropriately to make up for the salt lost by the human body due to sweating.
In addition, the human body is prone to lack of potassium in summer, making people feel tired and tired, and potassium tea is an excellent summer drink.
In the summer, eat fruits and vegetables with high water content, such as lettuce, cucumber, tomatoes, etc.; fresh fruits, such as peaches, apricots, watermelons, melons, etc., have a moisture content of 80% to 90%, which can be used to replenish water; dairy products can not only hydrate, but also meet the nutritional needs of the body.
In addition, people working in high temperature environments should appropriately supplement drinks containing elements such as potassium and magnesium.
Summer day and night is short, the temperature is high, the human body metabolism is strong, the consumption is also large, and it is easy to feel tired.
Adequate sleep can relax the brain and body systems, which is conducive to work and study, and is also a measure to prevent heat stroke.
Experts say that the best bedtime time is from 2200 to 23:00, and the best time to get up is from 5:30 to 6:30.
When sleeping, be careful not to lie under the air conditioning outlet and electric fan to avoid air conditioning disease and heat injury.
