Reported that the shared accommodation market has begun to pick up since March
The "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the National Information Center Sharing Economy Research Center recently showed that due to the impact of the epidemic, in the first five months of 2020, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market fell by 72.1% year-on-year.
However, the shared accommodation market has been warming since March, and the market turnover, order volume and reception number have gradually recovered.
The "Report" shows that the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market has dropped sharply, on the one hand, due to the sharp decline in travel and accommodation demand under the prevention and control of the epidemic, the sharp decrease in orders, the total number of orders in the first five months fell by 65% year-on-year, and the number of receptions fell by 63% year-on-year; on the other hand, the weak demand also led to a more significant decline in the price of inter-nights, and the average night price in the first five months fell by 16% year-on-on-on.
However, in March, April and May, the market turnover increased by 78%, 99% and 35% respectively; the number of orders increased by 141%, 52% and 50% respectively; the number of receptions increased by 81%, 12% and 28% respectively.
The report pointed out that the development of the shared accommodation industry has been optimistic for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, told the "Workers Daily" reporter that the development of shared accommodation needs stronger policy support, on the one hand, it is necessary to do a good job in the implementation of the policies that have been introduced in the early stage, further strengthen policy publicity, and focus on creating a better business environment; on the other hand, it is necessary to further increase policy guidance and support from stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovative service methods, and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform enterprises.
