The Zhengwan high-speed railway small Three Gorges Tunnel opened on the 26th.
Pictured through the scene.
Zhengwan high-speed rail from Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, to the southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, Hubei Province Xiangyang City to Chongqing Wanzhou District, the new line length of about 818 km, design speed of 350 km / h, Chongqing territory of about 184 km.
Among them, the Zhengzhou to Xiangyang section has been opened for operation on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
On the 26th, the whole line through the small Three Gorges Tunnel is the whole line control project of Zhengwan high-speed rail, and the project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to the survey and design side of China China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd. Zhengwan high-speed rail tunnel design responsible person Wang Jun, the location of the small Three Gorges tunnel terrain geological conditions are very complex, facing karst, sudden mud surge, soft rock deformation and other risks, is a class I high-risk tunnel, tunnel design and construction is extremely difficult.
"In the process of project construction, we used advanced geological forecasting such as geological survey method, material exploration method and advanced drilling method, and adopted a special design scheme for more than 30 kinds of caves. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was built, and a large cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel was designed and built," the Royal Army said.
According to the construction of the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction of the tunnel, the combination of dredging and blocking, through the construction of horizontal hole guidance, slurry blocking water, strengthening the tunnel structure support and the construction of sewage treatment station, not only to ensure the orderly progress of the project, but also to avoid the construction of drainage on the small Three Gorges scenic area of water damage, while successfully overcome the 7 km of soft rock deformation and other bad geology, daily maximum water up to 157,000 cubic meters of multi-stack water and other construction problems.
After the completion of the Zhengwan high-speed rail line, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger main channel to the central plains, north China and northeast China in the southwest region of China, which is of great significance to improving the capacity and quality of the northeast-to-east railway channel in the southwest region, improving the layout of the regional road network, accelerating the development of tourism resources along the route and the urbanization process, promoting regional coordinated development, and promoting the implementation of the western development strategy.
