Employment and price overall stability shows that the economy has a "temperature"
2020-07-26 07:01:37 Source: Economic Daily Author:Wang Sisuo Responsibility Editor:Wang Sisuo
The overall stability of employment and prices shows that the economy has a "temperature"
Economic Daily · China Economic Net reporter Lin Fangcan
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, China coordinated the promotion of epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development, the epidemic prevention and control situation continued to improve, the steady recovery of the economy was obvious, the employment and price performance closely related to people's livelihood were generally stable, and China's economy handed over a report card of economic operation with temperature.
In the first two months of this year, the survey unemployment rate increased.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of shutdown, the demand for employment of enterprises was reduced, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the unemployment rate of urban surveys increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the production and life order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Party Central Committee adheres to the general tone of steady progress, further strengthens macro policy hedging, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the assistance to stabilize the post and expand employment.
China has increased policy hedging and stable posts, played a combination of "relief and slow return" policy, phased relief of three social insurance units, allowing the extension of social insurance premiums, expanding the return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises, benefiting from the policy of job training, and giving absorption subsidies and trainee subsidies to enterprises to absorb key groups of employment.
With the implementation of various stable employment policies, the demand for employment in enterprises has steadily rebounded, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the unemployment rate of urban surveys has gradually declined, and in June, the survey unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Population and Employment Statistics Division of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to be effective, and the labor force that had withdrawn due to the impact of the epidemic in the early part of the year returned one after another, and the urban labor force participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, which was close to the level of the same period last year.
Data show that the total employment of cities and towns in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; the average weekly working time of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, an increase of 6.6 hours from February, and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices are equally related to thousands of households.
In January this year, the CPI rose by 5.4% year-on-year, a new high in many years.
Entering February, although the year-on-year increase in CPI fell slightly, it was still in the "5 range".
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, both the factors driving consumer demand before the Spring Festival, and the factors that drive the wrong month and the low base year-on-year basis of the Spring Festival.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, in January and February, there were logistics delays, untimely supply of materials, and increased cost of material transportation throughout the country, and some citizens were hoarded and snapped up, and the prices of some necessities increased significantly.
In order to cope with the disturbance caused by the price situation caused by the epidemic prevention and control, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation security to ensure the smooth transportation of materials.
Under the influence of a series of policy measures, the supply of vegetable melon and fruit market has been strongly guaranteed.
In order to cope with the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government introduced a policy to ensure stable supply and price, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, the supply of pork reserves was significantly improved, pig production capacity was restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and marketing was gradually normal.
Since March, pork prices have declined continuously, driving the year-on-year increase in food prices to 10.6% in May; in June, pork prices rose slightly month-on-month due to factors such as the slowdown in pig exports, reduced imports and the rebound in group consumption demand.
The seasonal changes in fresh vegetable prices are obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the higher base of the same period last year, the price of fresh fruit continued to decline year-on-year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic life of the masses has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation logistics, the supply and demand in various places have increased, and the supply and demand situation in the market has improved.
Since March, the CPI has declined for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also fallen from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the overall price level has recovered steadily.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level, and the overall inflation pressure is not large, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and life order under the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in the main producing areas of food, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on the behavior of disrupting market order such as hoarding and raising prices.
