The Lancet article praises China's anti-epidemic efforts to encourage countries to learn from the experience
As a country with a population of 1.4 billion people and a similar size to Europe or the United States, China has been effectively controlled at this stage, and there is no large-scale transmission, which has largely controlled the epidemic in China.
In the past decade, China has made significant investments in domestic research and public health construction, which has made China’s preparedness for the new crown much better than that year’s severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS).
The authors say that at the time of the SARS outbreak in 2002, China was initially ill-prepared, especially the pathogen could not be determined.
When the new coronavirus was discovered in December 2019, Chinese scientists were soon able to identify the virus species and shared genomic sequencing data with the international community on January 11, 2020.
By the end of January, doctors from mainland China and Hong Kong had clarified the clinical characteristics of the virus, warning the world of the threat of the new coronavirus through a research paper published in The Lancet.
China has also been at the forefront of vaccine research, under the state of emergency, through close domestic cooperation, such research is carried out very quickly and strictly, in May and July, respectively, in the Lancet announced the results of the progress of the early trials of the new crown vaccine developed in China.
China's experience shows that it is very important to invest in national health and research systems to effectively improve laboratory capabilities.
This is the basis for a rapid and effective national response to health emergencies and global health security.
Other countries, especially low- and middle-income countries, are well worth learning from.
In addition, China's experience proves that on the basis of strong research, it is necessary to make correct decisions with scientific evidence at a strong high level, so that the new crown epidemic can be effectively controlled.
Governments and their leaders must respect science, understand its values, and act on it in the best way for society.
In the early days of the outbreak, China National Health Construction appointed three groups of infectious disease experts to Wuhan to investigate the risk and spread of the new coronavirus, and their recommendations provided a basis for the decision of Wuhan to "close the city" on January 23; when some experts proposed the necessity and urgency of building a square cabin hospital, the government quickly made a decision and quickly implemented it; at the same time, the wide participation of the community and the masses also made the epidemic quickly and effectively controlled.
