Membrane separation technology helps to crack the "greenhouse effect"
Membrane separation technology helps to crack the "greenhouse effect"
New hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology diagram
Recently, the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University made significant progress in the "membrane separation method capture carbon dioxide", and successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology to greatly improve the carbon dioxide capture performance of film materials.
The results have been published as a cover article in the international journal Greenhouse Gas: Science and Technology.
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem plaguing human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the cause of the "greenhouse effect".
How to efficiently capture and utilize human emissions of carbon dioxide is the focus of scientists.
"Membrane separation method" is an emerging carbon dioxide capture technology, which separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials, and has the characteristics of high efficiency and simple operation.
How to make the membrane material "deep breath" and improve the efficiency of gas separation is a bottleneck in the use of membrane separation to capture carbon dioxide.
Tianjin University's scientific research team innovated ideas and explored the impact of different solvents on the separation performance of membrane gas through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that N-methylpyrrolidaneone as a preparation solvent, the carbon nanotubes in the resulting membrane material are more evenly distributed and "more breathable", which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of the film material.
With this new technology, the mixed matrix membrane, the carbon dioxide separation performance is close to the theoretical separation limit of such membrane materials.
“New technologies provide new ideas for membrane separation to capture CO2.”
Li Run, a member of the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team at Tianjin University, said: "We hope that this technology can provide strong support for future coal-fired power plants and chemical companies to deal with flue gas, and play a major role in controlling greenhouse gas emissions."
Before volunteering to fill in the report, first understand what is the professional grade difference - Sino-New Network
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning News Author: Yuxiao Responsibility Editor: Yuxiao
Before volunteering, you must first understand what is a professional grade difference.
Every year to fill in the college entrance examination volunteer, there are students or parents because of the lack of understanding of the noun involved in the voluntary filling, and thus affect the volunteer to fill in the report.
This year, five universities of Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued a 2020 admissions policy to cancel the professional grade difference.
What does it mean to have a professional grade difference, and what is the significance in voluntary reporting?
There are three ways of professional distribution rules.
Experts remind that before filling in the volunteer, we must read the admissions regulations of the school in detail and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the proportion of transfer and professional distribution rules.
Professional allocation rules refer to the three ways of professional priority, priority, and professional grade difference after the transfer of university files.
Which method of use of the university will be clear in the Admissions Charter.
However, there are also some colleges and universities that accept the principle of total score priority, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, the admission range of candidates in accordance with the total score line, when the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score line, it depends on whether the second professional volunteer admission score line, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer, there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" is that when the college arranges the candidate's major, according to one or several points published in the admissions charter to determine the admission of different professional candidates, this score value is "professional grade difference".
That is, the difference between the scores of the college in the admission of candidates for the first major and the non-first professional volunteer, and the difference between the volunteer grades of each professional, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 minute, etc.
For example.
Assume that students Xiaoming apply for A colleges and universities, the test has 560 points, and their professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce, A college professional admission to implement the professional grade difference method, the grade difference is divided into 2 points, 1 minute, 1 minute, 0 points.
In the professional distribution, if Xiaoming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the professional plan balance, then Xiaoming is admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted from 2 points, according to the 558 points and the first professional volunteer examination "international trade" candidates, to determine whether it meets the professional admission conditions; if it is still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted from 1 point (that is, 557 points).divided, and so on.
Different university professional grade settings are different
With the popularization of parallel volunteers, many colleges and universities have now canceled the professional grade difference, but this year there are still some universities still retain this method, from the school announced the "admission charter" point of view, this year, more than 20 universities have set up professional grade difference.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight College, etc.
In these colleges and universities, the professional grade difference set by each university is different.
Some colleges and universities in each major have grade difference, such as Ningxia University, the file has been sent to the school's candidates, according to the candidate to fill in the order of professional volunteers in order to reduce 1 point in order of admission.
Some universities have different professional grades between different majors.
For example, Jimei University, the total difference in professional volunteer grade difference is 4 points, that is, the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteer grade difference is 3 points, there is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, as parallel volunteers, other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteer grade difference is 1 point.
When filling in the volunteer, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school reported to be reported, to see if there is a professional grade difference, the form of grade difference is how, in the full consideration of the score at the same time, but also a reasonable analysis of the proposed school and professional, if the college in the admissions charter clearly adopts the grade difference method of admission, candidates in the choice of majors, pay attention to the gradient between the majors, improve the admission rate.
